X , Y
E[|aX+bY|] \leq |a|E[|X|]+|b|[E[|Y|]
a ,b \in \mathbb{R}
\mathbb{E} \| aX + bY \| = \int \| aX + bY \| \leqslant \int \|aX\| + \|bY\| 
 = \|a\| \int \|X\| + \|b\| \int \|Y\| = \|a\|\mathbb{E}\|X\| + \|b\|\mathbb{E}\|Y\|
\mathbb{E}[X] = \int_\Omega X\ \mathrm{d}P
\mathbb{E}[X] = \sum_{k \in \mathrm{Cod}(k)}k\cdot P(X = k)
\mathbb{E}[X] = \sum_{\omega \in \Omega}X(\omega) \cdot P(\omega)
